definitions.definition: To prepare curds for making cheese.
( technology ) To make holes in a pattern of circuitry to decrease pattern density.
( slang ) To smile excessively, as for a camera.

main_definition: To prepare curds for making cheese.
secondary_definitions: ( technology ) To make holes in a pattern of circuitry to decrease pattern density.
( slang ) To smile excessively, as for a camera.

definitions.definition: ( slang ) To stop; to refrain from.
examples: Cheese your patter! (= stop talking, shut up)

definitions.definition: ( slang ) To anger or irritate someone, usually in combination with "off".
examples: All this waiting around is really cheesing me off.

main_definition: ( slang ) To stop; to refrain from.
secondary_definitions: ( slang ) To anger or irritate someone, usually in combination with "off".

definitions.definition: To use a controversial or unsporting tactic to gain an advantage (especially in a game.)
examples: You can cheese most of the game using certain exploits.

definitions.definition: To use an unconventional , all-in strategy to take one's opponent by surprise early in the game (especially for real-time strategy games).

main_definition: ( Internet slang , gaming , ambitransitive ) To use a controversial or unsporting tactic to gain an advantage (especially in a game.)
